# Step 1: Create the S3 Bucket

On the AWS Console, Search S3 and Create bucket.
Name the bucket and choose the region you have been using.
Leave rest of the settings as default.

# Step 2: Upload files for Website

Create two HTML files on your computer: one named index.html and another named error.html (Use VSCode for this)
Within the bucket, click upload and select your HTML files and then click upload on the bottom of the page.

My code for index.html:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My AWS Website</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Hello from AWS!</h1>

<p>Static Website hosted on S3</p>

</body>
</html>

My code for error.html:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Error</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>404</h1>

<p>Page Not Found</p>

</body>
</html>

# Step 3: Enable Static Website Hosting

Within the bucket, head to Properties-Static Website Hosting-Edit
Choose the following: Enable, Hosting type= Host a Static website, choose your index and error document and then save the changes.
A website endpoint will appear, this will not need to be tested as of yet due to the bucket being private.

# Step 4: Make Objects Public

Within the bucket, head to Permissions and Disable Block Public Access-Edit-Untick: Block all public access.
Confirm and save.
Head to Bucket policy within Permissions and paste JSON information. Change where it says my-static-website-12345 with the name of your bucket.
{
  "Version":"2012-10-17",
  "Statement":[
    {
      "Sid":"PublicRead",
      "Effect":"Allow",
      "Principal":"*",
      "Action":"s3:GetObj# ect",
      "Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::my-static-website-12345/*"
    }
  ]
}
Click Save changes.

# Step 5: CloudFront Distribution

Search CloudFront and then Create distribution.
Name the distribution and then go Next.
For the Origin ID, enter your website endpoint which can be found in the following: Your S3 Bucket- Properties- Static Website Hosting.
Go to Customize Origin settings and then go to Protocol: HTTP only.
Go to Customize Cache settings and select: redirect Redirect HTTP to HTTPS, Allowed HTTP methods: GET, HEAD
For Cache policy, choose: Managed-CachingOptimized
Click next until you are on the final page then create the distribution.
Click edit to edit the Default root and enter in index.html

# Step 6: Test CloudFront Website

Copy and Paste your Distribution domain name into a browser search bar and click enter.
Your website should now appear.
